  "body": "For some reasons, people like to discuss the number of immutable and mutable bindings in Rust codes: [example 1](https://www.reddit.com/r/rust/comments/3sf823/observations_bindings_immutable_by_default/), [example 2](https://www.reddit.com/r/rust/comments/3srvz0/ideas_about_features_which_may_be_useful_for_rust/). People's first impression is that mutable bindings are common; then invariably, experienced Rust users report that they are not. Numbers like 5%, 10%, 20% are thrown around. Since the compiler knows the answer, let's make it available.\n\nRunning this on core, std, syntax reports that 20%, 22%, 17% of local bindings are mutable, confirming the folklore.\n",
